licting layers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCulture conflictzKenyazSamburu District. 0aFood habitszKenyazSamburu District. 0aFood preferenceszKenyazSamburu District. 0aFoodxSymbolic aspectszKenyazSamburu District. 0aSamburu (African people)xDomestic animals. 0aSamburu (African people)xFood. 0aSamburu (African people)xSocial conditions. 0aSocial changezKenyazSamburu District. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aafrican culture.  aagricultural products.  aagriculture.  aanthropology.  abasic diet.  ablood.  acattle.  acultural studies.  aeating.  aethnography.  afamines.  afood.  agastronomy.  agovernment food.  agray food.  akenya.  akenyan culture.  aloikop.  alokop.  ameat.  amilk.  amoral decay.  anilotic people.  anorth central kenya.  anorthern kenya.  apastoralists.  asamburu cattle herders.  asamburu culture.  asamburu material life.  asamburu social life.  asamburu tribe.  asamburu.  aselfishness.  asemi nomadic.  astruggle for food.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094482440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944824423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944824/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles